  ],
  "faq": [
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Which phrases help most for a first trip to South Korea?",
        "zh-CN": "第一次去韩国旅行，最值得先准备哪类短语？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Transport phrases are the fastest win because they cover airport rail, subway exits, T-money, and taxis. Add dining and hotel phrases next for check-in, cafes, and restaurant orders.",
        "zh-CN": "最优先的是交通短语，因为机场铁路、地铁出口、T-money 和打车都会马上用到。接着补上酒店和餐饮短语，就能覆盖入住、咖啡店和餐厅点单。"
      }
    },
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Is English enough in South Korea, or should I keep Korean phrases ready?",
        "zh-CN": "在韩国旅行只靠英语够吗，还是要准备韩语短语？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "English works in many hotels and tourist areas, but short Korean phrases still help a lot for subway questions, taxi rides, kiosks, and neighborhood restaurants.",
        "zh-CN": "在酒店和热门景点附近英语通常够用，但地铁问路、打车、自助点餐机和社区餐厅里，备几句韩语短语会明显更顺利。"
      }
    }
  ]
}
